==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paraxylene
<hw>Par`a*xy"lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A hydrocarbon (<chform>C6H4(CH3)2</chform>) of the aromatic series
obtained as a colorless liquid by the distillation of camphor with zinc
chloride. It is one of the three metamers of xylene. Cf.
<er>Metamer</er>, and <er>Xylene</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parboil</ent>⟦br⟧
